\chapter{Startup: U1.SYSTEM}

After the kernel relocates itself into the language card and builds its
global page at [[MLI]]--\,[[$BFFF]], ProDOS scans the volume directory
for the first file whose name ends in \texttt{.SYSTEM} and runs it at
[[$2000]]. On this disk that is \texttt{U1.SYSTEM}, the game's
launcher. It has three jobs:

\begin{enumerate}
\item Show the title banner (``Ultima I --- The First Age of
  Darkness'').
\item Install a resident \textbf{file-access library} at
  [[$B700]]--[[$BAFF]] --- a compact wrapper around the ProDOS MLI
  providing BLOAD/BRUN/BSAVE-style calls with inline arguments. The
  game proper uses this library for every disk access, which is why it
  is installed below the kernel and protected in the system bitmap
  rather than kept inside the launcher.
\item Set the ProDOS prefix to the game volume and \textsc{brun} the
  startup file --- \texttt{U1.INTRO} by default, or whatever pathname
  a program selector placed in the startup buffer.
\end{enumerate}

\section{Defines}

<<u1system defines>>=
; --- Monitor zero page and ROM entry points ---
MON_CH          EQU $24         ; text cursor column
MON_A1          EQU $3C         ; monitor source start pointer
MON_A2          EQU $3E         ; monitor source end pointer
MON_A4          EQU $42         ; monitor destination pointer
RESET_VEC       EQU $03F2       ; warm-reset vector
MON_SETTXT      EQU $FB39       ; text mode
MON_TABV        EQU $FB5B       ; set text row from A
ROM_MACHID      EQU $FBB3       ; ROM identification byte ($06 = IIe+)
MON_HOME        EQU $FC58       ; clear screen
MON_WAIT        EQU $FCA8       ; delay ~(26+27A+5A^2)/2 microseconds
MON_PRBYTE      EQU $FDDA       ; print A as two hex digits
MON_COUT        EQU $FDED       ; character out
MON_CROUT       EQU $FD8E       ; print carriage return
MON_MOVE        EQU $FE2C       ; block move (A1..A2) -> (A4)
MON_SETKBD      EQU $FE89       ; IN#0
MON_SETVID      EQU $FE93       ; PR#0
SPEAKER         EQU $C030       ; speaker toggle
SET_STDZP       EQU $C008       ; main-bank zero page/stack
SET_ALTZP       EQU $C009       ; aux-bank zero page/stack
; --- ProDOS global page ---
MLI             EQU $BF00       ; MLI call entry
GP_DEVNUM       EQU $BF30       ; last-used device (unit number)
GP_BITMAP_B0    EQU $BF6E       ; system bitmap, pages $B0-$B7
GP_BITMAP_B8    EQU $BF6F       ; system bitmap, pages $B8-$BF
GP_MACHID       EQU $BF98       ; machine id byte
GP_IBAKVER      EQU $BFFC       ; interpreter compatibility version
GP_IVERSION     EQU $BFFD       ; interpreter version
; --- Fixed buffers ---
