\section{The address tables}

Four look-up tables turn coordinates into screen addresses.
[[HGR_ROW_LO]]/[[HGR_ROW_HI]] give the base address of each of the
192 hi-res scanlines on page 1 (every consumer EORs the high byte
with [[ZP_PAGE_XOR]] to hit the draw page). The text routines index
them by $8\times$\,row; [[PLOT]] indexes them by pixel row plus
[[$10]], because the pixel-graphics viewport starts 16 scanlines
down, under the screen border.

For [[PLOT]], pixel column $x$ (0--255) maps through [[XCOL_TBL]]
(screen byte offset \emph{plus one} --- a zero entry marks the column
off-limits, and the offset is one-based because the viewport starts
at screen byte 1) and [[XMASK_TBL]] (the bit within that byte, with
bit 7 always set so the palette bit is preserved by the masked
write).

